model.name: NIK-dependent p100 processing into p52 with RelB binding and IkBd degradation, mass action, SBML 2v4

body.p: This model represents NIK-dependent p100 processing into p52 followed by binding to RelB and NIK-dependent IkBd degradation. This model assesses the impact of substrate complex competition on RelB-p52.

rdf:Description.dcterms:description: Substrate complex competition is a regulatory motif that allows NFκB RelA to license but not amplify NFκB RelB
